Beyond Meatâ€™s ability to replicate meaty layers out of plant matter is among the companyâ€™s greatest trade secrets â€” what puts it in a different category, perhaps, than the long line of faux meats that have come before. Biz Stone, one of Twitterâ€™s founders and a Beyond Meat backer, described the companyâ€™s fake chicken to Fast Company as having a meaty mouth feel. â€œIt feels fatty and muscly and like itâ€™s not good for you when youâ€™re chewing it,â€ Stone said in 2012. â€œFor a long-time vegan, itâ€™s a little bit freaky.â€
