Sea creatures will move away from the increasingly warm waters in the tropics â€” endangering the way of life for fishing-dependent communities â€” and toward the poles, where theyâ€™ll encounter other creatures, both predator and prey. Some newly arrived species will flourish, others will probably go extinct.
